        <abstract>
            <p>Asks CD’s views on TR’s observations that leaves breathe from their under-surfaces.</p>
            <p>Peach-trees in hothouses cannot be kept in health unless fresh air is admitted so as to make its way under the leaves.</p>
            <p>Continues his observations on the effect of environment on men – those migrating to America gradually assuming Indian-like features.</p>
        </abstract>
